	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.54]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Like shamans, I think pallys get a bad rap.&nbsp;&nbsp;Yeah, they fall short in a lot of ways I'll be the first to say, but it's moreso a problem that most players and groups don't know how to use them. <br><br>In most cases I find the best use of a pally is as a backup tank.  The tank and pally stay in constant communication.  The pally interupts the casters and can cure the main tank if diseased, poisoned, etc., as well as dispell.  <br><br>Pallys are very self sufficient.  Since they share a lot of abilities with clerics they can alleviate some of the burden off the cleric by healing themselves.  Slow but sure.  But again, if the cleric doesn't let the pally fill this role and blows his mana on heals for you, then the pally's advantages are wasted.  <br><br>If the new line of stun spells (lower level, short casting time) comes out with luclin, it looks like pallys will be the ultimate caster interupters.  Mem a couple stun spells and that combined with bash should shut down just about any casting mob out there.  It will also make them quite deadly to casters in pvp.  <br><br>I guess I can imagine it being tough to find a suitable role for a pally in the very high level raid game, but then again, 99% of *any* character class will never see that anyway.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
