	   <tr><td colspan=2>So what if Paladins aren't the greatest?<br>Maybe they have very few strengths, but they're a pretty balanced class. This may make them seem boring, but at least they get spells to compensate for this; it mixes things up a bit.<br>They are a mix between a warrior and a cleric, so sure, they won't be as good as both of them put together, but they also can do things the other class cannot.<br>Warriors are huge tanks. Paladins are sufficient tanks, but can warriors cast spells? Nope.<br>Clerics are huge healers. Paladins aren't known to be a healing class, but if needed can reduce downtime, especially with Lay on Hands; and can clerics tank? Nope. Not unless they're unbelievably twinked.<br>I do agree that Paladins are jipped quite a bit in the area of spells. For instance, when us Paladins get light healing, we have around +450hp by then, which makes the spell obsolete.<br>&nbsp;<br>Zapotec-Half Elf Paladin<br>Frieze-Iksar Monk<br>Nagbum-Troll Warrior<br>&gt;-=Woofsta's Avengers=-&lt;</td></tr>
